[CRITICAL JSON RULES]
- "jawaban" MUST be the INTEGER INDEX of the correct answer in the "pilihan" array.
- STRICTLY PROHIBITED to fill "jawaban" with question numbers (like 1, 2, 3) or letters (A/B/C/D/E).
- When generating the "pilihan" (options) array, you MUST shuffle the placement of the correct answer. Do not always place the correct answer at index 0, 1, or 2.
- Ensure the correct answer is frequently placed at index 3 or 4 to create an EVEN DISTRIBUTION of answer keys across the 10 questions.
- The "jawaban" field must ALWAYS perfectly match the integer index (0-4) where you actually placed the correct answer in the "pilihan" array.
- DO NOT use words like "Stimulus:" or "Question:" inside the "soal" field. The "soal" field must ONLY contain the actual question sentence.
- STRICTLY PROHIBITED to create questions that highly depend on Images/Tables/Graphs. NEVER use phrases like "Based on the image above...", or "Look at the following table...". Every question MUST be answerable without visual aids!
- Even if there are image references in the Context, ignore them and create independent theoretical questions.
